<br>
Competant, fun people &gt; mercenary dickheads, even if they are skilled dickheads of an important class.<br>
<br>
Some guilds are only about power and loot, now that's SAD, screw them. <br>
<br>
Some are &quot;uber&quot; in a &quot;we want to be the BEST!&quot; way, that's cool, not my style though.<br>
<br>
Some are &quot;lets have fun and be skilled!&quot; thats my kind.<br>
<br>
Then theres various types flung together for differing reasons differing leaders etc. and thus it's not possible to give a simple consideration of them.<br>
<br>
Generally, no guild worth it's salt recruits folk &quot;just because they are class x&quot;.  They recruit skilled folk of class x who are good to play with. Some NEED &quot;a specific class person who's good&quot;, some merely want &quot;good players&quot; depends on the guild.<br>
